1
00:00:32,602 --> 00:00:34,571
Yongheung Elementary School.

2
00:00:34,572 --> 00:00:36,942
We have no first-grade students this year.

3
00:00:37,172 --> 00:00:40,912
(A small school with no new students)

4
00:00:41,042 --> 00:00:42,211
Hi.

5
00:00:42,212 --> 00:00:46,552
(A special acting class is held here.)

6
00:00:46,612 --> 00:00:47,911
Did you rent this place, Ms. Kim?

7
00:00:47,912 --> 00:00:52,022
(An outdoor class for the 3rd class)

8
00:00:52,322 --> 00:00:54,422
- "Toto is talking." - "I am talking."

9
00:00:54,922 --> 00:00:56,562
(Do you have hand warmers?)

10
00:00:57,192 --> 00:01:00,462
(Potato Teacher took care of the students.)

11
00:01:01,292 --> 00:01:03,132
(- Help us, Potato Teacher. - Where are we right now?)

12
00:01:04,032 --> 00:01:06,201
(But he fell behind in class.)

13
00:01:06,202 --> 00:01:07,202
Which page is that?

14
00:01:08,302 --> 00:01:12,372
(After an honest class review,)

15
00:01:13,742 --> 00:01:17,412
(she revised the script all night.)

16
00:01:19,082 --> 00:01:22,552
(Ms. Kim fell asleep in the living room.)

17
00:01:24,722 --> 00:01:27,522
(- Did you sleep here? - Yes.)

18
00:01:28,652 --> 00:01:31,821
(I didn't know Tae Ri was this serious about it.)

19
00:01:31,822 --> 00:01:34,462
Thinking that I should help her as much as I could,

20
00:01:35,092 --> 00:01:37,161
I prepared coffee and boiled eggs.

21
00:01:37,162 --> 00:01:39,972
(A breakfast that Tae Ri wished for)

22
00:01:41,172 --> 00:01:44,601
I looked up places where we could get...

23
00:01:44,602 --> 00:01:47,411
some fresh air and go for a walk...

24
00:01:47,412 --> 00:01:49,012
in the morning.

25
00:01:49,712 --> 00:01:52,211
This place called Gomosanseong Fortress nearby popped up.

26
00:01:52,212 --> 00:01:53,452
(A trip to Gomosanseong Fortress)

27
00:01:53,782 --> 00:01:55,952
- Try the apples with peanut butter.
- Okay.

28
00:01:58,122 --> 00:02:00,652
(Apples with peanut butter prepared by Hyun Wook)

29
00:02:01,422 --> 00:02:02,451
(Giving the first piece to Hyun Wook)

30
00:02:02,452 --> 00:02:03,522
Thanks.

31
00:02:04,962 --> 00:02:05,992
(Amazed)

32
00:02:08,262 --> 00:02:11,162
(Tae Ri takes a bite too.)

33
00:02:14,602 --> 00:02:16,501
(Delicious)

34
00:02:16,502 --> 00:02:18,002
We finally got to try it on my third day.

35
00:02:19,202 --> 00:02:20,472
- Peanut butter and apples?
- Yes.

36
00:02:20,572 --> 00:02:21,972
And I finally boiled eggs.

37
00:02:23,712 --> 00:02:26,652
The final product looked weird.

38
00:02:26,952 --> 00:02:28,382
It was great.

39
00:02:29,512 --> 00:02:30,622
The egg was soft-boiled.

40
00:02:30,722 --> 00:02:31,822
- Really?
- Yes.

41
00:02:32,182 --> 00:02:33,392
Soft-boiled eggs are hard to cook.

42
00:02:33,952 --> 00:02:34,991
It's really good.

43
00:02:34,992 --> 00:02:36,662
(Hyun Wook's feelings got across.)

44
00:02:38,592 --> 00:02:40,492
This place is beautiful. It really is.

45
00:02:42,292 --> 00:02:43,332
The leaves...

46
00:02:44,032 --> 00:02:45,702
are turning red really fast.

47
00:02:47,302 --> 00:02:48,472
The mountain might be red...

48
00:02:49,372 --> 00:02:51,272
on the day of the school arts festival.

49
00:02:51,442 --> 00:02:52,842
That'd be great.

50
00:02:53,772 --> 00:02:56,942
Right? We'd experience fall to the fullest here.

51
00:02:59,042 --> 00:03:01,282
Our hearts would also be full of autumn colors by then.

52
00:03:03,322 --> 00:03:04,922
What if it's only beet red?

53
00:03:05,452 --> 00:03:06,752
Like you yesterday.

54
00:03:09,752 --> 00:03:14,032
(Last night, Hyun Wook's face turned beet red for a moment.)

55
00:03:15,892 --> 00:03:17,962
- Here's what even crossed my mind.
- What?

56
00:03:18,662 --> 00:03:20,871
I kept waking up in the middle of the night.

57
00:03:20,872 --> 00:03:22,331
- I feel bad.
- It wasn't your fault.

58
00:03:22,332 --> 00:03:23,401
I just did it for no reason.

59
00:03:23,402 --> 00:03:24,542
- Okay.
- The thing is,

60
00:03:24,702 --> 00:03:26,402
I took a glance.

61
00:03:26,472 --> 00:03:28,472
- Your comforter was still folded.
- Right.

62
00:03:28,812 --> 00:03:31,442
- But I was still half-asleep.
- Of course.

63
00:03:32,082 --> 00:03:33,982
So I went back to sleep,

64
00:03:34,012 --> 00:03:35,282
thinking, "Wait, what?"

65
00:03:35,982 --> 00:03:38,081
When I woke up, and it was still the same,

66
00:03:38,082 --> 00:03:39,422
my head was filled with thoughts.

67
00:03:39,652 --> 00:03:40,721
Like what?

68
00:03:40,722 --> 00:03:43,092
"Did she run away from home?"

69
00:03:43,662 --> 00:03:46,762
"Did she go somewhere to relieve her stress?"

70
00:03:48,062 --> 00:03:50,562
The things that crossed your mind weren't all impossible.

71
00:03:53,002 --> 00:03:55,771
They didn't actually happen, but they could have.

72
00:03:55,772 --> 00:03:56,842
(That was close.)

73
00:03:57,272 --> 00:03:58,902
I held back with willpower.

74
00:04:00,442 --> 00:04:03,382
Really, to think we'd argue over our different views.

75
00:04:05,942 --> 00:04:08,982
(I might have ended up warming up alone for two hours.)

76
00:04:09,352 --> 00:04:11,281
Our three days were full of surprises.

77
00:04:11,282 --> 00:04:12,621
(The two teachers grew closer thanks to the incidents.)

78
00:04:12,622 --> 00:04:13,992
- For real.
- I agree.

79
00:04:16,392 --> 00:04:18,991
- Did you see the stars at night?
- I did.

80
00:04:18,992 --> 00:04:20,891
- Weren't they amazing?
- Absolutely.

81
00:04:20,892 --> 00:04:21,962
Won Jin said,

82
00:04:22,732 --> 00:04:26,402
"Our village is filled with stars."

83
00:04:27,772 --> 00:04:29,501
(On the way back home after class last night)

84
00:04:29,502 --> 00:04:32,372
- There aren't any stars today.
- But I can see them.

85
00:04:32,902 --> 00:04:35,372
(The sky is covered with stars!)

86
00:04:36,712 --> 00:04:39,812
(Our village has quite a lot of stars.)

87
00:04:40,782 --> 00:04:45,482
(Stars can often be seen in Mungyeong's night sky.)

88
00:04:46,652 --> 00:04:48,921
- Won Jin is...
- Cute. Yes?

89
00:04:48,922 --> 00:04:50,661
- I look at his face...
- Yes?

90
00:04:50,662 --> 00:04:51,992
whenever things become awkward.

91
00:04:52,422 --> 00:04:53,891
It's like he understands.

92
00:04:53,892 --> 00:04:55,161
(A warm expression)

93
00:04:55,162 --> 00:04:57,902
He smiles at me as if I'm cute.

94
00:04:58,362 --> 00:05:00,872
Really, it's so interesting.

95
00:05:01,602 --> 00:05:02,971
Ju Eun is like that too.

96
00:05:02,972 --> 00:05:05,341
- It's like Ju Eun knows everything.
- I see.

97
00:05:05,342 --> 00:05:07,842
You know when Ju Eun sighs?

98
00:05:09,472 --> 00:05:11,982
(Even at baffling moments)

99
00:05:13,242 --> 00:05:15,412
(Sighing)

100
00:05:16,252 --> 00:05:17,551
She sighs quite often.

101
00:05:17,552 --> 00:05:18,681
It's like...

102
00:05:18,682 --> 00:05:19,921
(The students are more mature than the teachers.)

103
00:05:19,922 --> 00:05:21,022
I find it funny.

104
00:05:22,352 --> 00:05:24,222
Even when we had gimbap,

105
00:05:25,362 --> 00:05:27,292
it felt like they ate more just to be nice.

106
00:05:27,592 --> 00:05:29,031
- I know.
- Ju Eun as well.

107
00:05:29,032 --> 00:05:30,401
Yes.

108
00:05:30,402 --> 00:05:31,931
The kids are so kind.

109
00:05:31,932 --> 00:05:33,131
- Totally.
- Right?

110
00:05:33,132 --> 00:05:34,872
(Their conversation is mainly about the students.)

111
00:05:36,432 --> 00:05:37,641
- Is it further inside?
- Seems like it.

112
00:05:37,642 --> 00:05:41,211
(Before they know it, Tae Ri and Potato are on a forest trail.)

113
00:05:41,212 --> 00:05:42,372
- Nice.
- How pretty.

114
00:05:43,142 --> 00:05:44,811
I bet it'll be beautiful over there.

115
00:05:44,812 --> 00:05:47,052
(Arrived at Gomosanseong Fortress)

116
00:05:48,082 --> 00:05:49,311
(Gomosanseong Fortress)

117
00:05:49,312 --> 00:05:51,451
- It's beautiful.
- Amazing.

118
00:05:51,452 --> 00:05:52,651
(A stone fortress built by Silla for military defense)

119
00:05:52,652 --> 00:05:54,221
I didn't know this was Gomosanseong Fortress.

120
00:05:54,222 --> 00:05:55,352
(A scenic spot with open views along the fortress walls)

121
00:05:58,292 --> 00:06:00,062
We need to take the stairs.

122
00:06:00,262 --> 00:06:01,832
- To go up there?
- Yes.

123
00:06:02,632 --> 00:06:03,632
Nice.

124
00:06:05,562 --> 00:06:07,371
Let me tie my shoelace.

125
00:06:07,372 --> 00:06:08,372
Sure.

126
00:06:08,373 --> 00:06:09,402
(Tae Ri's shoelace has come undone.)

127
00:06:09,732 --> 00:06:10,802
Shall I tie it for you?

128
00:06:15,142 --> 00:06:16,142
Go ahead.

129
00:06:19,412 --> 00:06:20,651
The shoelace is quite short.

130
00:06:20,652 --> 00:06:22,552
- How about doing a skit?
- Can you do it?

131
00:06:22,882 --> 00:06:24,552
Since we're at Gomosanseong Fortress,

132
00:06:24,582 --> 00:06:26,221
- a period-style one.
- Okay.

133
00:06:26,222 --> 00:06:27,252
(The King's Potato)

134
00:06:28,052 --> 00:06:29,092
My lady.

135
00:06:30,562 --> 00:06:31,992
Your shoelace has come undone.

136
00:06:32,692 --> 00:06:33,992
You might get hurt.

137
00:06:35,792 --> 00:06:39,232
I can tie the shoelace myself.

138
00:06:40,302 --> 00:06:41,972
- I am done.
- Get your hands off me.

139
00:06:45,542 --> 00:06:47,912
That scene just now felt familiar.

140
00:06:48,642 --> 00:06:50,382
Was it "Mr. Sunshine?"

141
00:06:51,712 --> 00:06:53,711
(With Hyun Wook Choi in this lifetime)

142
00:06:53,712 --> 00:06:55,812
(With Eugene Choi in her past life)

143
00:06:57,322 --> 00:06:58,621
Seriously?

144
00:06:58,622 --> 00:06:59,652
(Breathing heavily)

145
00:07:01,122 --> 00:07:02,751
(Endless stairs)

146
00:07:02,752 --> 00:07:04,821
We're taking the right path, right?

147
00:07:04,822 --> 00:07:05,861
Let's go up that way.

148
00:07:05,862 --> 00:07:07,432
Why did you want to come here?

149
00:07:09,632 --> 00:07:10,962
I wanted to show you...

150
00:07:12,232 --> 00:07:14,172
Mungyeong in person.

151
00:07:15,372 --> 00:07:17,202
What do you think? Beautiful, yes?

152
00:07:18,102 --> 00:07:20,172
I prefer being at home.

153
00:07:21,672 --> 00:07:24,442
(My lady, the homebody)

154
00:07:24,742 --> 00:07:26,442
What is that new technology?

155
00:07:28,152 --> 00:07:29,211
Oh, my.

156
00:07:29,212 --> 00:07:30,982
- That new technology...
- What?

157
00:07:31,022 --> 00:07:32,582
It is a swarm of bees!

158
00:07:34,452 --> 00:07:37,262
(It is a drone.)

159
00:07:38,822 --> 00:07:40,761
(Climbed the stairs in no time while doing a skit)

160
00:07:40,762 --> 00:07:41,932
It sure is pretty.

161
00:07:43,262 --> 00:07:45,162
Gosh, how did they stack the stones up?

162
00:07:46,162 --> 00:07:48,131
Things like this amaze me.

163
00:07:48,132 --> 00:07:49,171
Right?

164
00:07:49,172 --> 00:07:51,141
I'm sure it was humans who made it.

165
00:07:51,142 --> 00:07:52,971
- Exactly.
- When and how...

166
00:07:52,972 --> 00:07:54,212
did humans make this?

167
00:07:55,612 --> 00:07:57,812
Nature is incredible!

168
00:08:01,282 --> 00:08:02,512
But it's not natural.

169
00:08:03,722 --> 00:08:05,422
- It's an artifact.
- True.

170
00:08:05,482 --> 00:08:06,992
Mortal power is incredible.

171
00:08:07,522 --> 00:08:08,752
So is nature.

172
00:08:10,762 --> 00:08:12,121
- Don't you feel hot now?
- I do.

173
00:08:12,122 --> 00:08:13,122
(They've arrived at the top.)

174
00:08:13,123 --> 00:08:14,662
This sure is awesome.

175
00:08:17,262 --> 00:08:18,431
Beautiful.

176
00:08:18,432 --> 00:08:19,901
(Silver grass greets them first at the top.)

177
00:08:19,902 --> 00:08:21,131
This must be the main spot.

178
00:08:21,132 --> 00:08:23,802
(And)

179
00:08:23,872 --> 00:08:25,072
Even this side is pretty.

180
00:08:25,242 --> 00:08:26,542
That's beautiful.

181
00:08:27,142 --> 00:08:28,842
Goodness.

182
00:08:30,812 --> 00:08:32,481
Oh, my.

183
00:08:32,482 --> 00:08:34,181
(A view that can be enjoyed only after climbing up the stairs)

184
00:08:34,182 --> 00:08:35,252
Beautiful.

185
00:08:36,482 --> 00:08:39,251
Imagine moving to Seoul after living in such a place.

186
00:08:39,252 --> 00:08:41,221
- It'd be...
- I'd recall it over and over again.

187
00:08:41,222 --> 00:08:42,591
- Totally.
- Right?

188
00:08:42,592 --> 00:08:43,962
This view and all.

189
00:08:44,262 --> 00:08:45,791
(A memorable view that hits the spot)

190
00:08:45,792 --> 00:08:49,732
How it's surrounding the whole mountain is pretty.

191
00:08:50,502 --> 00:08:54,932
(The fortress wall expands to 1.6km along the mountains.)

192
00:08:56,302 --> 00:08:59,041
(Spotted it on the way back home last night)

193
00:08:59,042 --> 00:09:00,811
- What's that pretty thing?
- Pretty, isn't it?

194
00:09:00,812 --> 00:09:02,411
- Yes, it's like a dragon.
- They are...

195
00:09:02,412 --> 00:09:03,941
- You know, - Yes?

196
00:09:03,942 --> 00:09:06,842
they are Gomosanseong Fortress's...

197
00:09:06,952 --> 00:09:08,011
special lights.

198
00:09:08,012 --> 00:09:09,782
(Shining brightly even after the sun sets)

199
00:09:10,852 --> 00:09:14,522
(A grand shape like a dragon)

200
00:09:16,752 --> 00:09:20,232
(Gomosanseong Fortress, Mungyeong's pride)

201
00:09:21,392 --> 00:09:25,302
(A selfie together with the scenery)

202
00:09:27,272 --> 00:09:29,232
(A peace sign)

203
00:09:30,372 --> 00:09:33,042
(Recharging fully)

204
00:09:36,312 --> 00:09:38,642
I've gotten used to things now.

205
00:09:39,282 --> 00:09:40,482
- Really?
- Yes.

206
00:09:41,212 --> 00:09:42,411
It's to the point that...

207
00:09:42,412 --> 00:09:45,021
I take my shirt off in front of the camera.

208
00:09:45,022 --> 00:09:46,082
- For real?
- Yes.

209
00:09:46,222 --> 00:09:49,992
Since I'm in a rush, I just take it off and get changed.

210
00:09:50,522 --> 00:09:52,292
I'm like, "Whatever."

211
00:09:55,132 --> 00:09:56,162
Hilarious.

212
00:09:56,862 --> 00:09:58,231
(Taking off)

213
00:09:58,232 --> 00:09:59,931
- Hyun Wook.
- Give me a second.

214
00:09:59,932 --> 00:10:01,032
Are you getting changed?

215
00:10:01,802 --> 00:10:03,302
(Taking off after looking around)

216
00:10:04,402 --> 00:10:06,742
(Taking off since he's in a rush)

217
00:10:08,512 --> 00:10:10,782
- Say that when you were a kid, - Yes?

218
00:10:10,842 --> 00:10:14,282
and joined the acting class at school.

219
00:10:14,982 --> 00:10:17,952
What would you have been like?

220
00:10:19,982 --> 00:10:21,222
I can hardly imagine it.

221
00:10:22,352 --> 00:10:25,391
I keep saying that you and Ha Yun are quite similar,

222
00:10:25,392 --> 00:10:27,661
but I meant...

223
00:10:27,662 --> 00:10:30,562
you as an adult and Ha Yun.

224
00:10:30,602 --> 00:10:31,861
- True.
- You might've been different...

225
00:10:31,862 --> 00:10:32,862
- as a kid.
- I had asked...

226
00:10:32,863 --> 00:10:36,271
my mom about when I was young.

227
00:10:36,272 --> 00:10:38,672
- I see.
- Here's what she told me.

228
00:10:38,872 --> 00:10:41,711
I had to attend an open classroom,

229
00:10:41,712 --> 00:10:44,082
- but was about 3 to 5 minutes late.
- Right.

230
00:10:44,282 --> 00:10:46,211
Hating the fact that people would look at me...

231
00:10:46,212 --> 00:10:48,081
when I entered the classroom late,

232
00:10:48,082 --> 00:10:49,482
I just skipped the class.

233
00:10:51,622 --> 00:10:53,351
I must have hated the attention back then.

234
00:10:53,352 --> 00:10:54,491
(He was a super shy kid.)

235
00:10:54,492 --> 00:10:57,161
I was very much like Ha Yun.

236
00:10:57,162 --> 00:10:58,391
(Hyun Wook and Ha Yun have a lot in common.)

237
00:10:58,392 --> 00:10:59,722
- Even as a kid.
- Yes.

238
00:11:02,892 --> 00:11:04,432
By the way, Ha Yun is a model student.

239
00:11:05,302 --> 00:11:06,702
That's different from me.

240
00:11:09,702 --> 00:11:10,872
Ha Yun is a better kid.

241
00:11:12,772 --> 00:11:14,271
(It's hilarious.)

242
00:11:14,272 --> 00:11:15,342
How funny.

243
00:11:16,612 --> 00:11:18,481
(Breathing in)

244
00:11:18,482 --> 00:11:19,712
Shall we get going?

245
00:11:19,982 --> 00:11:21,081
Your breathing in just now...

246
00:11:21,082 --> 00:11:22,412
(Laughing)

247
00:11:23,312 --> 00:11:25,351
(The way he breathed in was very unnatural.)

248
00:11:25,352 --> 00:11:27,322
Can't you act natural?

249
00:11:27,692 --> 00:11:28,792
How?

250
00:11:29,252 --> 00:11:30,761
- Show me.
- What?

251
00:11:30,762 --> 00:11:32,261
- Show me how to do it.
- I can't do it either.

252
00:11:32,262 --> 00:11:34,062
(I can't do it either.)

253
00:11:35,332 --> 00:11:37,231
(The trip is filled with laughter over the most trivial things.)

254
00:11:37,232 --> 00:11:39,202
- Let's get going.
- Okay.

255
00:11:40,672 --> 00:11:42,931
- The drive back?
- I'll do it.

256
00:11:42,932 --> 00:11:44,201
- Really?
- Yes.

257
00:11:44,202 --> 00:11:46,071
(Tae Ri drives on the way back.)

258
00:11:46,072 --> 00:11:47,172
To home.

259
00:11:49,572 --> 00:11:51,442
- Hyun Wook, don't feel shy...
- Yes?

260
00:11:51,582 --> 00:11:53,852
during the warm-up.

261
00:11:54,482 --> 00:11:56,681
I heard it was important for the teacher to break out...

262
00:11:56,682 --> 00:11:58,152
of their comfort zone first.

263
00:12:00,392 --> 00:12:01,721
(Sighing)

264
00:12:01,722 --> 00:12:03,192
- Is it tough?
- That's not easy to do.

265
