438
00:19:24,732 --> 00:19:26,031
Merry Christmas.

439
00:19:26,032 --> 00:19:28,931
Kids, how was the warm-up? Good?

440
00:19:28,932 --> 00:19:30,271
- Yes.
- Yes.

441
00:19:30,272 --> 00:19:34,172
Okay, now then. Gather around with your scripts.

442
00:19:35,472 --> 00:19:37,141
(Trudging)

443
00:19:37,142 --> 00:19:38,782
- I'm hit with reality.
- What?

444
00:19:39,012 --> 00:19:40,041
I'm hit with reality.

445
00:19:40,042 --> 00:19:41,051
- Why?
- Are you hit with reality?

446
00:19:41,052 --> 00:19:42,211
- You did well, so how come?
- Being the Wizard...

447
00:19:42,212 --> 00:19:43,382
hits me with reality.

448
00:19:44,252 --> 00:19:45,322
I don't have it.

449
00:19:46,082 --> 00:19:47,752
- I can't do it.
- Are you hit with reality?

450
00:19:48,252 --> 00:19:49,791
Why?

451
00:19:49,792 --> 00:19:51,361
Being the Wizard hits me with reality.

452
00:19:51,362 --> 00:19:54,362
The Wizard? Do you have no confidence in being one?

453
00:19:54,762 --> 00:19:56,432
The Wizard is Kyung Mo.

454
00:19:56,532 --> 00:19:57,631
(The Wizard during yesterday's reading)

455
00:19:57,632 --> 00:20:00,102
The Wizard is even the Gatekeeper.

456
00:20:00,602 --> 00:20:02,001
"Willing to sacrifice..."

457
00:20:02,002 --> 00:20:06,301
"for his friends, the Tin Man..."

458
00:20:06,302 --> 00:20:08,672
"will be warm-hearted."

459
00:20:09,542 --> 00:20:10,982
- "Is warm-hearted." - "Is warm-hearted."

460
00:20:12,082 --> 00:20:16,812
(The Wizard's lines are too long for Kyung Mo.)

461
00:20:18,422 --> 00:20:21,122
(And...)

462
00:20:21,892 --> 00:20:26,322
(Ha Yun has always been a bit too shy.)

463
00:20:27,292 --> 00:20:31,262
(The teachers had a discussion about their roles that night.)

464
00:20:32,302 --> 00:20:34,331
(But the problem is...)

465
00:20:34,332 --> 00:20:36,672
(what to do with Ha Yun and Kyung Mo.)

466
00:20:37,402 --> 00:20:40,272
(How to help them project their voices.)

467
00:20:41,542 --> 00:20:45,182
(They've been thinking hard about their roles.)

468
00:20:46,012 --> 00:20:49,882
We have to make this happen in a short time.

469
00:20:50,952 --> 00:20:53,421
What do we need the most?

470
00:20:53,422 --> 00:20:54,492
(They must assign the roles today.)

471
00:20:54,592 --> 00:20:56,122
- Kids!
- Yes?

472
00:20:56,222 --> 00:20:58,421
Today, I have the most exciting...

473
00:20:58,422 --> 00:21:00,462
and dynamic scene.

474
00:21:00,562 --> 00:21:03,632
It is the scene of the Wicked Witch of the West.

475
00:21:03,962 --> 00:21:06,502
There are lots of characters in this scene.

476
00:21:07,972 --> 00:21:13,771
(They face a crisis because of the Witch.)

477
00:21:13,772 --> 00:21:15,641
But the Wizard isn't in it,

478
00:21:15,642 --> 00:21:16,642
so one person doesn't have a role.

479
00:21:16,742 --> 00:21:18,281
So, I'll designate...

480
00:21:18,282 --> 00:21:20,082
one narrator and one Witch.

481
00:21:20,282 --> 00:21:22,012
- Okay.
- Okay.

482
00:21:22,252 --> 00:21:23,552
I'll tell you why we do it this way.

483
00:21:24,322 --> 00:21:26,752
Before the break,

484
00:21:27,052 --> 00:21:29,251
you will take a vote on...

485
00:21:29,252 --> 00:21:32,222
who is a better fit for each role,

486
00:21:32,322 --> 00:21:33,561
including yourself.

487
00:21:33,562 --> 00:21:35,992
Write your opinions and give them to me,

488
00:21:36,092 --> 00:21:39,402
and Potato Teacher and I will have a discussion...

489
00:21:39,932 --> 00:21:42,972
to assign the roles that you've been waiting for.

490
00:21:43,072 --> 00:21:45,171
- Your roles will be decided today.
- It will start soon.

491
00:21:45,172 --> 00:21:48,071
- Yes. Are you excited?
- All right? Give it up.

492
00:21:48,072 --> 00:21:49,742
- I hope I'm the Lion.
- Aren't you excited?

493
00:21:50,612 --> 00:21:53,312
- I hope I'm Dorothy.
- I'll change it up.

494
00:21:53,412 --> 00:21:55,151
First, the narrator.

495
00:21:55,152 --> 00:21:56,381
(Announcing the temporary roles)

496
00:21:56,382 --> 00:21:58,021
The narrator will be Ju Eun.

497
00:21:58,022 --> 00:21:59,381
It should be a girl.

498
00:21:59,382 --> 00:22:01,552
The Witch is Ha Yun.

499
00:22:01,652 --> 00:22:03,491
(Terrified)

500
00:22:03,492 --> 00:22:05,122
The Scarecrow is Eun Soo.

501
00:22:05,992 --> 00:22:08,432
The Tin Man is Do Hyun.

502
00:22:09,032 --> 00:22:11,561
- The Lion is Won Jin.
- Yes!

503
00:22:11,562 --> 00:22:13,161
Toto is Kyung Mo!

504
00:22:13,162 --> 00:22:15,732
- Yes! I'm fine with Toto.
- Dorothy is Hyo Min.

505
00:22:17,472 --> 00:22:20,772
- Dorothy is Hyo Min.
- Oh, no!

506
00:22:21,142 --> 00:22:22,742
I had a feeling he'd be Dorothy.

507
00:22:23,272 --> 00:22:26,081
Scene number three, the story begins...

508
00:22:26,082 --> 00:22:27,812
in a dark forest.

509
00:22:27,912 --> 00:22:29,482
Toto, say your line.

510
00:22:31,052 --> 00:22:34,392
"Sniff, sniff, I smell fire."

511
00:22:35,222 --> 00:22:36,222
Adorable.

512
00:22:37,452 --> 00:22:40,192
"Don't tell me you're the Wicked Witch of the West."

513
00:22:40,292 --> 00:22:41,292
Dun dun dun!

514
00:22:41,992 --> 00:22:43,092
Ha Yun, you're the Witch.

515
00:22:43,532 --> 00:22:46,562
- It's Ha Yun.
- Do I have to do it?

516
00:22:46,902 --> 00:22:48,732
- Of course.
- Switch with me.

517
00:22:50,532 --> 00:22:51,641
(Shy)

518
00:22:51,642 --> 00:22:53,702
Ha Yun, you're embarrassed, right? Do you want me to do it?

519
00:22:54,142 --> 00:22:55,912
No, it's Ha Yun's turn.

520
00:22:56,672 --> 00:22:58,542
Can I do it for him?

521
00:22:58,742 --> 00:23:00,311
- He can't...
- He can do it.

522
00:23:00,312 --> 00:23:02,612
Ha Yun, you can just say it in your normal voice.

523
00:23:02,882 --> 00:23:04,882
- Right, no pressure.
- As if you're talking.

524
00:23:05,182 --> 00:23:07,251
"I finally meet you, Dorothy."

525
00:23:07,252 --> 00:23:09,752
"I knew you'd be on your way to meet the Wizard of Oz."

526
00:23:09,922 --> 00:23:12,892
"What I want is your silver shoes."

527
00:23:13,562 --> 00:23:16,062
"What? I can't give you my shoes for that reason!"

528
00:23:16,792 --> 00:23:18,131
"The Witch spits fire!"

529
00:23:18,132 --> 00:23:19,462
"Spit, spit."

530
00:23:20,232 --> 00:23:21,631
(Shy)

531
00:23:21,632 --> 00:23:23,371
- The Tin Man...
- That was good.

532
00:23:23,372 --> 00:23:25,401
- That was great, Ha Yun.
- "She spat fire..."

533
00:23:25,402 --> 00:23:26,501
"to Dorothy and her friends."

534
00:23:26,502 --> 00:23:28,712
"Dorothy is taken by the Witch."

535
00:23:28,812 --> 00:23:30,512
"The Tin Man shouts!"

536
00:23:30,812 --> 00:23:32,342
"Dorothy!"

537
00:23:32,782 --> 00:23:35,281
"As the suspenseful music builds to a crescendo,"

538
00:23:35,282 --> 00:23:36,512
"the curtain drops."

539
00:23:36,612 --> 00:23:38,752
"The curtain opens,"

540
00:23:38,852 --> 00:23:41,392
"and there's a large lake at the center."

541
00:23:41,492 --> 00:23:44,051
"On one side of the lake, Dorothy and the Witch..."

542
00:23:44,052 --> 00:23:45,922
"are still quarreling."

543
00:23:46,022 --> 00:23:49,532
"Dorothy's friends belatedly arrive across the lake."

544
00:23:49,692 --> 00:23:51,202
"The Lion is crying."

545
00:23:51,502 --> 00:23:54,972
"No, Dorothy."

546
00:23:55,272 --> 00:23:57,432
- "Yes, go and get Dorothy." - "Dorothy."

547
00:23:57,842 --> 00:24:01,312
"How should I get rid of the Witch and get Dorothy back?"

548
00:24:01,912 --> 00:24:03,442
"Let's save her!"

549
00:24:04,782 --> 00:24:08,211
"I will be a bridge so that you can cross..."

550
00:24:08,212 --> 00:24:10,152
"this lake."

551
00:24:10,482 --> 00:24:11,582
"You can't."

552
00:24:11,752 --> 00:24:16,752
"Once your body touches water,"

553
00:24:17,962 --> 00:24:19,521
"Your whole body will get rusty."

554
00:24:19,522 --> 00:24:22,762
"your whole body will get rusty, and you will freeze..."

555
00:24:23,032 --> 00:24:27,402
- "Forever." - "And you will freeze forever."

556
00:24:27,702 --> 00:24:29,971
"Guys,"

557
00:24:29,972 --> 00:24:31,442
"I will cross the lake."

558
00:24:32,042 --> 00:24:34,572
"The Lion jumps over the lake."

559
00:24:34,772 --> 00:24:38,482
"He and Dorothy work together to shove the Witch."

560
00:24:38,682 --> 00:24:41,112
"The Witch falls into the lake, and everyone shouts."

561
00:24:41,312 --> 00:24:43,351
Everyone, in 1, 2, 3.

562
00:24:43,352 --> 00:24:45,782
- "Yes, the Lion has done it!" - "Yes, the Lion has done it!"

563
00:24:45,882 --> 00:24:48,191
- "Thank you, Lion!" - "Thank you, Lion!"

564
00:24:48,192 --> 00:24:49,422
(Still in character as the Tin Man)

565
00:24:53,662 --> 00:24:56,831
- That was fun.
- Okay, that was great.

566
00:24:56,832 --> 00:24:58,401
- Did you all listen?
- Yes.

567
00:24:58,402 --> 00:25:01,232
I'll give out the ballot paper for the roles.

568
00:25:01,332 --> 00:25:04,702
You can vote for your friends and yourself, okay?

569
00:25:05,172 --> 00:25:07,072
Let's try assigning the roles.

570
00:25:07,502 --> 00:25:09,672
You can write your name on the character that you want.

571
00:25:10,272 --> 00:25:12,612
- Your name...
- Do I have to write a reason?

572
00:25:12,842 --> 00:25:14,981
Yes, if you write the reasons,

573
00:25:14,982 --> 00:25:16,351
it'll help us, the teachers,

574
00:25:16,352 --> 00:25:18,021
- decide on the roles.
- Right.

575
00:25:18,022 --> 00:25:19,522
But I don't have to if I can't think of any?

576
00:25:20,222 --> 00:25:21,222
You can't think of any reasons?

577
00:25:21,223 --> 00:25:22,651
- Toto and...
- Fine.

578
00:25:22,652 --> 00:25:24,292
But it will be great if you write them.

579
00:25:25,622 --> 00:25:27,091
It's tough, isn't it?

580
00:25:27,092 --> 00:25:30,392
(They discreetly vote until the last moment.)

581
00:25:30,632 --> 00:25:35,032
- Oh, my gosh.
- The first period is over.

582
00:25:35,872 --> 00:25:36,901
If you're done,

583
00:25:36,902 --> 00:25:39,142
- you can hand me the slips.
- It's a secret.

584
00:25:39,442 --> 00:25:41,842
- Are you done?
- Yes.

585
00:25:42,272 --> 00:25:43,772
I'm done!

586
00:25:44,212 --> 00:25:45,282
Thank you.

587
00:25:45,982 --> 00:25:47,012
Thanks.

588
00:25:47,212 --> 00:25:48,911
Have fun out there, guys.

589
00:25:48,912 --> 00:25:49,981
We'll have a discussion.

590
00:25:49,982 --> 00:25:51,782
(Time to assign the roles)

591
00:25:53,222 --> 00:25:54,991
Let's read what they wrote and see if they have...

592
00:25:54,992 --> 00:25:56,422
- Yes.
- any different opinions.

593
00:25:58,692 --> 00:26:00,392
Eun Soo got the most votes for Dorothy.

594
00:26:01,232 --> 00:26:02,732
- Eun Soo?
- Eun Soo.

595
00:26:03,732 --> 00:26:06,231
- Really?
- Five. No, four.

596
00:26:06,232 --> 00:26:07,232
(Eun Soo got the most votes for Dorothy.)

597
00:26:07,402 --> 00:26:08,532
Who's this?

598
00:26:09,502 --> 00:26:11,131
- Who wrote this?
- I'm not sure.

599
00:26:11,132 --> 00:26:13,271
(Cho Ha Yun)

600
00:26:13,272 --> 00:26:14,711
I bet this is Ha Yun.

601
00:26:14,712 --> 00:26:15,972
He didn't write the reasons under his name.

602
00:26:18,512 --> 00:26:19,882
- See?
- That's so cute.

603
00:26:20,882 --> 00:26:23,151
- Let's give him the role he wants.
- What he wants?

604
00:26:23,152 --> 00:26:24,311
- Okay.
- Right?

605
00:26:24,312 --> 00:26:25,382
Yes, let's give him that.

606
00:26:26,582 --> 00:26:29,822
(The Wizard and the Gatekeeper: Ha Yun)

607
00:26:31,462 --> 00:26:33,961
Do Hyun played the Tin Man pretty well, right?

608
00:26:33,962 --> 00:26:35,762
Do Hyun played the Tin Man well.

609
00:26:38,002 --> 00:26:39,401
He wrote, "I want it."

610
00:26:39,402 --> 00:26:41,702
He wrote that he wanted the Tin Man's role.

611
00:26:42,172 --> 00:26:43,202
No way.

612
00:26:44,502 --> 00:26:45,602
That's amazing.

613
00:26:48,912 --> 00:26:51,482
No one's ever said they wanted a role before.

614
00:26:51,942 --> 00:26:52,942
I got chills.

615
00:26:55,852 --> 00:26:58,222
This has to be Ju Eun's, right?

616
00:26:58,782 --> 00:26:59,782
- Yes.
- Are you sure?

617
00:26:59,783 --> 00:27:01,321
Yes, I'm positive.

618
00:27:01,322 --> 00:27:02,322
(Ju Eun must play the Witch.)

619
00:27:02,992 --> 00:27:04,892
She got all the votes.

620
00:27:05,322 --> 00:27:06,422
What do we have left?

621
00:27:06,522 --> 00:27:08,761
Toto, the Scarecrow, and the Lion.

622
00:27:08,762 --> 00:27:10,362
(There are three roles left.)

623
00:27:11,362 --> 00:27:14,632
I think Hyo Min will be good.

624
00:27:14,832 --> 00:27:17,001
Right? I don't think he'll play...

625
00:27:17,002 --> 00:27:18,941
any other roles poorly.

626
00:27:18,942 --> 00:27:21,102
(Hyo Min can pull off almost any role.)

627
00:27:22,042 --> 00:27:23,712
- But Kyung Mo...
- Who?

628
00:27:23,812 --> 00:27:24,812
Kyung Mo.

629
00:27:25,612 --> 00:27:27,482
- Kyung Mo? Really?
- Yes.

630
00:27:27,942 --> 00:27:29,182
This is Kyung Mo's.

631
00:27:32,022 --> 00:27:33,221
- Really?
- Yes.

632
00:27:33,222 --> 00:27:35,491
Do you think he can do a good job of playing this role?

633
00:27:35,492 --> 00:27:36,652
I'm not sure.

634
00:27:39,022 --> 00:27:40,622
No, it has to be Kyung Mo.

635
00:27:40,822 --> 00:27:42,292
I think he's the right fit for this role.

636
00:27:43,132 --> 00:27:44,362
- Which one?
- This one.

637
00:27:44,462 --> 00:27:45,501
(Will Kyung Mo get the role he wants?)

638
00:27:45,502 --> 00:27:48,472
It looks all right to me. It looks good.

639
00:27:48,572 --> 00:27:50,202
- And Kyung Mo...
- I think he can pull it off.

640
00:27:50,302 --> 00:27:53,302
Otherwise, he has no other roles to play.

641
00:27:55,242 --> 00:27:57,711
(Doing a final check before the announcement)

642
00:27:57,712 --> 00:27:58,712
Okay.

643
00:28:01,852 --> 00:28:04,512
Yes, I like it.

644
00:28:04,782 --> 00:28:05,981
So, this is fixed.

645
00:28:05,982 --> 00:28:07,522
- It's going all the way.
- Yes.

646
00:28:10,122 --> 00:28:14,062
(What roles will they get?)

647
00:28:15,792 --> 00:28:18,801
Kids, take your seats.

648
00:28:18,802 --> 00:28:21,002
- Take your seats.
- I'm in my seat.

649
00:28:21,102 --> 00:28:22,102
Are you?

650
00:28:22,702 --> 00:28:25,072
We're going to announce your roles now.

651
00:28:25,172 --> 00:28:28,411
Potato Teacher will...

652
00:28:28,412 --> 00:28:30,511
announce your roles 1 by 1.

653
00:28:30,512 --> 00:28:31,841
- Okay.
- Okay.

654
00:28:31,842 --> 00:28:34,041
The roles you get today are final. Is that all right?

655
00:28:34,042 --> 00:28:35,312
- Yes.
- Go!

656
00:28:35,952 --> 00:28:36,952
All right.

657
00:28:36,953 --> 00:28:38,051
(Announcing the first role)

658
00:28:38,052 --> 00:28:41,452
Now, he's going to describe the role with his body.

659
00:28:42,252 --> 00:28:43,322
The Tin Man.

660
00:28:43,422 --> 00:28:46,992
The Tin Man is Do Hyun!

661
00:28:47,092 --> 00:28:48,691
Oh, my gosh!

662
00:28:48,692 --> 00:28:49,831
(The Tin Man: Do Hyun)

663
00:28:49,832 --> 00:28:51,631
Give it up!

664
00:28:51,632 --> 00:28:53,562
Is it possible that I'm the Lion?

665
00:28:53,962 --> 00:28:57,432
Next, the Lion.

666
00:28:58,072 --> 00:28:59,941
Drum rolls.

667
00:28:59,942 --> 00:29:01,241
The Lion is Won Jin.

668
00:29:01,242 --> 00:29:02,671
Won Jin!

669
00:29:02,672 --> 00:29:05,342
(The Lion: Won Jin)

670
00:29:06,442 --> 00:29:09,152
Next, Dorothy.

671
00:29:09,312 --> 00:29:10,681
Dorothy.

672
00:29:10,682 --> 00:29:12,351
(Dorothy)

673
00:29:12,352 --> 00:29:13,751
Eun Soo!

674
00:29:13,752 --> 00:29:15,821
(Dorothy: Eun Soo)

675
00:29:15,822 --> 00:29:18,762
Congratulations. Next...

676
00:29:19,562 --> 00:29:22,291
I'll point at the one playing the Witch and the narrator.

677
00:29:22,292 --> 00:29:24,561
Yes, please do. Drum rolls.

678
00:29:24,562 --> 00:29:27,301
- The Witch and the narrator...
- The Witch, the narrator...

679
00:29:27,302 --> 00:29:29,072
go to not Ha Yun.

680
00:29:29,172 --> 00:29:30,371
It's Ju Eun.

681
00:29:30,372 --> 00:29:33,541
(The Witch, Munchkin, the narrator: Ju Eun)

682
00:29:33,542 --> 00:29:35,241
- Ha Yun, were you excited?
- No.

683
00:29:35,242 --> 00:29:37,642
You play the Munchkin as well.

684
00:29:37,842 --> 00:29:39,982
- Give it up!
- You were really good.

685
00:29:40,812 --> 00:29:41,912
Show her some support.

686
00:29:42,352 --> 00:29:43,352
Next...

687
00:29:43,353 --> 00:29:45,322
(There are three roles left.)

688
00:29:45,982 --> 00:29:46,982
The Scarecrow.

689
00:29:47,452 --> 00:29:50,452
The Scarecrow. Drum rolls!

690
00:29:50,792 --> 00:29:54,021
Hyo Min is the Scarecrow!

691
00:29:54,022 --> 00:29:56,291
- The Scarecrow?
- That was close.

692
00:29:56,292 --> 00:29:58,861
Give him a big round of applause!

693
00:29:58,862 --> 00:29:59,862
(Clapping)

694
00:29:59,863 --> 00:30:02,071
- Next...
- Toto?

695
00:30:02,072 --> 00:30:03,401
(There are Toto and the Wizard left.)

696
00:30:03,402 --> 00:30:05,441
- Toto.
- Announce it.

697
00:30:05,442 --> 00:30:07,441
- Toto is...
- Toto.

698
00:30:07,442 --> 00:30:09,972
- Drum rolls.
- It can't be me.

699
00:30:10,412 --> 00:30:11,442
Kyung Mo!

700
00:30:11,912 --> 00:30:13,582
Toto is Kyung Mo.

701
00:30:14,042 --> 00:30:16,612
But there's only the Gatekeeper left.

702
00:30:16,782 --> 00:30:18,781
- The Wizard and the Gatekeeper.
- It must be Ha Yun, then.

703
00:30:18,782 --> 00:30:21,222
- Even better.
- The Gatekeeper is Ha Yun.

704
00:30:22,992 --> 00:30:24,821
(The final cast of "The Wizard of Oz")

705
00:30:24,822 --> 00:30:26,291
(Eun Soo)

706
00:30:26,292 --> 00:30:27,761
(Kyung Mo)

707
00:30:27,762 --> 00:30:29,591
(Hyo Min)

708
00:30:29,592 --> 00:30:31,091
(Won Jin)

709
00:30:31,092 --> 00:30:32,831
(Do Hyun)

710
00:30:32,832 --> 00:30:34,231
(Ju Eun)

711
00:30:34,232 --> 00:30:38,872
(Ha Yun)

712
00:30:39,842 --> 00:30:41,542
What role do you want to play?

713
00:30:42,042 --> 00:30:43,342
Dorothy.

714
00:30:44,242 --> 00:30:45,612
The Wicked Witch of the West.

715
00:30:46,482 --> 00:30:48,751
The Tin... No, the Lion.

716
00:30:48,752 --> 00:30:50,482
(Most of them got the roles they wanted.)

717
00:30:52,222 --> 00:30:55,792
(But Hyo Min doesn't seem to like his role.)

718
00:30:57,692 --> 00:30:58,991
(She senses his disappointment.)

719
00:30:58,992 --> 00:31:02,062
One second, guys.

720
00:31:02,492 --> 00:31:04,391
Although you're not saying it out loud,

721
00:31:04,392 --> 00:31:07,101
some of you are happy with your roles,

722
00:31:07,102 --> 00:31:09,232
while some of you aren't.

723
00:31:09,602 --> 00:31:12,271
But let's keep practicing...

724
00:31:12,272 --> 00:31:14,642
and have fun while acting out the scenes.

725
00:31:14,742 --> 00:31:18,441
And once you realize the character's true charm...

726
00:31:18,442 --> 00:31:19,741
and how fun it is to play it,

727
00:31:19,742 --> 00:31:22,812
it'll be a lot more fun.

728
00:31:23,382 --> 00:31:25,321
Let's have faith. It's only begun.

729
00:31:25,322 --> 00:31:27,322
We have 7 to 8 days left.

730
00:31:27,482 --> 00:31:28,992
We'll see how it goes then.

731
00:31:29,492 --> 00:31:31,521
I'm serious. Give me some credit.

732
00:31:31,522 --> 00:31:32,591
(Hoping everyone will have fun)

733
00:31:32,592 --> 00:31:34,392
All right?

734
00:31:34,522 --> 00:31:35,562
- Okay.
- Okay?

735
00:31:35,662 --> 00:31:37,091
I hope you...

736
00:31:37,092 --> 00:31:40,732
- help me out and trust me, okay?
- Okay.

737
00:31:41,002 --> 00:31:43,232
- Okay.
- Let's unite with faith.

738
00:31:44,202 --> 00:31:47,471
Let's share our impressions today.

739
00:31:47,472 --> 00:31:50,611
We couldn't do it after the outdoor class yesterday,

740
00:31:50,612 --> 00:31:53,211
so I'd like you to share your impressions today.

741
00:31:53,212 --> 00:31:54,212
Won Jin, you can go first.

742
00:31:55,212 --> 00:31:58,321
I've been wanting to play the Lion,

743
00:31:58,322 --> 00:32:01,082
and it makes me happy that I got the role.

744
00:32:01,522 --> 00:32:02,922
You're happy.

745
00:32:03,792 --> 00:32:05,422
- Next, Kyung Mo.
- Yes!

746
00:32:05,492 --> 00:32:07,561
Is there anyone you want to compliment today?

747
00:32:07,562 --> 00:32:10,192
(Who does Kyung Mo want to compliment?)

748
00:32:11,562 --> 00:32:12,832
(Pointing)

749
00:32:14,102 --> 00:32:15,102
(He compliments Hyo Min.)

750
00:32:15,103 --> 00:32:16,232
Hyo Min?

751
00:32:16,532 --> 00:32:20,742
Because he played Toto really well.

752
00:32:20,842 --> 00:32:23,242
- For playing Toto well.
- Yes.

753
00:32:23,312 --> 00:32:25,641
That's true. Hyo Min played Toto so well.

754
00:32:25,642 --> 00:32:28,712
That means you'll have to work harder to play Toto, right?

755
00:32:29,982 --> 00:32:31,111
(Smiling)

756
00:32:31,112 --> 00:32:32,522
Next, Hyo Min.

757
00:32:33,352 --> 00:32:35,852
The outdoor class yesterday was fun.

758
00:32:36,322 --> 00:32:37,891
And I want to compliment...

759
00:32:37,892 --> 00:32:38,962
(Kyung Mo)

760
00:32:39,422 --> 00:32:40,422
(Hyo Min compliments Kyung Mo.)

761
00:32:40,423 --> 00:32:41,522
You complimented each other.

762
00:32:42,432 --> 00:32:44,291
Because he played the Wizard well.

763
00:32:44,292 --> 00:32:45,661
Yes, he did.

764
00:32:45,662 --> 00:32:47,502
I had a reality check, though.

765
00:32:47,902 --> 00:32:49,472
You did?

766
00:32:51,002 --> 00:32:52,202
Next, Do Hyun.

767
00:32:52,572 --> 00:32:54,772
I was fine with any roles,

768
00:32:56,012 --> 00:32:59,112
but I was glad that I got the part...

769
00:32:59,482 --> 00:33:01,381
as the Tin Man.

770
00:33:01,382 --> 00:33:03,012
And I want to compliment Noh Hyo Min.

771
00:33:03,212 --> 00:33:04,212
Hyo Min?

772
00:33:04,213 --> 00:33:06,081
(Do Hyun compliments Hyo Min.)

773
00:33:06,082 --> 00:33:09,392
He seemed sad for not getting Toto's role.

774
00:33:09,792 --> 00:33:11,861
- You wanted to cheer him up.
- Yes.

775
00:33:11,862 --> 00:33:13,021
Next, Ju Eun.

776
00:33:13,022 --> 00:33:14,022
(Hyo Min secretly wanted to play Toto.)

777
00:33:14,023 --> 00:33:17,361
During the outdoor class yesterday,

778
00:33:17,362 --> 00:33:19,532
I really enjoyed the box lunch.

779
00:33:20,062 --> 00:33:22,801
I especially liked the tuna gimbap.

780
00:33:22,802 --> 00:33:23,971
It was good.

781
00:33:23,972 --> 00:33:24,972
Thank you, ma'am.

782
00:33:24,972 --> 00:33:25,972
(Ms. Ju Eun's compliment)

783
00:33:25,973 --> 00:33:27,102
- He was the chef.
- Yes.

784
00:33:28,712 --> 00:33:30,672
My impressions on yesterday and today...

785
00:33:30,942 --> 00:33:35,112
I feel like we grew closer in a short time,

786
00:33:35,482 --> 00:33:37,351
so I'm exhilarated.

787
00:33:37,352 --> 00:33:38,581
How about you?

788
00:33:38,582 --> 00:33:39,582
- Good.
- Great.

789
00:33:39,583 --> 00:33:40,651
- Yes!
- I also had a good feeling.

790
00:33:40,652 --> 00:33:43,722
And I want to compliment...

791
00:33:44,692 --> 00:33:46,962
You can praise yourselves.

792
00:33:48,292 --> 00:33:51,702
- Well done, me!
- Everyone, compliment yourself.

793
00:33:52,502 --> 00:33:55,801
Hyo Min, compliment yourself, okay?

794
00:33:55,802 --> 00:33:58,031
- Well done, me!
- Compliment yourself.

795
00:33:58,032 --> 00:34:00,071
(Hyo Min showed tears in the meantime.)

796
00:34:00,072 --> 00:34:01,642
- All right?
- Okay.

797
00:34:02,212 --> 00:34:03,312
Oh, no.

798
00:34:05,412 --> 00:34:07,982
I feel conflicted.

799
00:34:12,822 --> 00:34:16,652
Hyo Min, will you talk to me after class?

800
00:34:16,752 --> 00:34:18,591
Just for a minute.

801
00:34:18,592 --> 00:34:19,592
(Nodding)

802
00:34:19,593 --> 00:34:21,861
All right, class. Great job today.

803
00:34:21,862 --> 00:34:23,431
That's it for today.

804
00:34:23,432 --> 00:34:24,661
- Thank you!
- Thank you!

805
00:34:24,662 --> 00:34:26,401
- Thank you!
- You can take these home.

806
00:34:26,402 --> 00:34:27,831
Okay.

807
00:34:27,832 --> 00:34:29,271
How did you do it in such a short time?

808
00:34:29,272 --> 00:34:30,972
- I'll carry it.
- All done.

809
00:34:32,942 --> 00:34:35,141
What about the question notes?

810
00:34:35,142 --> 00:34:37,511
I don't have much time right now,

811
00:34:37,512 --> 00:34:40,182
so I'll write them at home and bring them back.

812
00:34:40,712 --> 00:34:42,211
Just in case...

813
00:34:42,212 --> 00:34:45,851
Kids, I'll write the answers on your question notes,

814
00:34:45,852 --> 00:34:47,521
and give them back tomorrow, okay?

815
00:34:47,522 --> 00:34:48,522
(The question notes will be covered next time.)

816
00:34:48,922 --> 00:34:50,122
The question notes...

817
00:34:50,892 --> 00:34:53,362
Goodbye, Ms. Kim. See you tomorrow.

818
00:34:53,722 --> 00:34:55,461
- Bye, Won Jin.
- Bye.

819
00:34:55,462 --> 00:34:56,932
I'll walk you out.

820
00:34:57,232 --> 00:34:58,402
Do you want to go with me?

821
00:34:58,662 --> 00:34:59,731
Today's class is over.

822
00:34:59,732 --> 00:35:01,001
- Hyo Min and I...
- Bye-bye.

823
00:35:01,002 --> 00:35:02,272
will have a chat.

824
00:35:03,232 --> 00:35:04,802
- Hyo Min.
- Yes?

825
00:35:05,902 --> 00:35:07,202
Was it that sad?

826
00:35:08,912 --> 00:35:11,012
Sit here for a second.

827
00:35:13,342 --> 00:35:15,482
Do you know why...

828
00:35:15,812 --> 00:35:17,482
Well, you're really good at playing Toto.

829
00:35:17,582 --> 00:35:18,851
You were so good.

830
00:35:18,852 --> 00:35:22,491
When we read it yesterday, you were so good...

831
00:35:22,492 --> 00:35:24,451
that I laughed out loud so hard. You know that, right?

832
00:35:24,452 --> 00:35:26,322
I laughed really hard.

833
00:35:26,592 --> 00:35:28,121
That means...

834
00:35:28,122 --> 00:35:31,462
that you can pull off any roles.

835
00:35:31,932 --> 00:35:34,961
I know that you can perfectly play any role you're given...

836
00:35:34,962 --> 00:35:36,402
once you do your best.

837
00:35:36,572 --> 00:35:39,172
You'd be a great fit for all seven roles.

838
00:35:40,442 --> 00:35:43,041
But your classmates also need...

839
00:35:43,042 --> 00:35:44,772
roles to play.

840
00:35:44,972 --> 00:35:47,281
But Toto's lines...

841
00:35:47,282 --> 00:35:51,111
are easy and repetitive.

842
00:35:51,112 --> 00:35:54,281
And you showed me such great acting,

843
00:35:54,282 --> 00:35:56,521
so I thought you could pull it off.

844
00:35:56,522 --> 00:35:58,621
It was a very hard decision for me as well.

845
00:35:58,622 --> 00:36:01,622
It broke my heart when I saw you cry.

846
00:36:02,632 --> 00:36:03,662
I'm really sorry.

847
00:36:04,162 --> 00:36:07,132
But the truth is...

848
00:36:07,162 --> 00:36:09,801
it's because I know you can do well.

849
00:36:09,802 --> 00:36:12,401
If I thought you wouldn't be able to pull it off,

850
00:36:12,402 --> 00:36:13,702
I wouldn't even give it to you.

851
00:36:14,772 --> 00:36:15,842
Right?

852
00:36:15,972 --> 00:36:18,742
Does that make sense? I mean it.

853
00:36:19,012 --> 00:36:20,712
It's because you're too good.

854
00:36:21,482 --> 00:36:24,011
I hope you trust me and focus on this role.

855
00:36:24,012 --> 00:36:26,751
The Scarecrow is a very difficult role!

856
00:36:26,752 --> 00:36:27,781
(Hoping he'll see what she means)

857
00:36:27,782 --> 00:36:30,592
And you can do it so well.

858
00:36:31,422 --> 00:36:33,862
Don't tell your friends that I cried, okay?

859
00:36:34,322 --> 00:36:35,391
Okay?

860
00:36:35,392 --> 00:36:36,591
You can't tell anyone.

861
00:36:36,592 --> 00:36:39,331
I need to have dignity in class.

862
00:36:39,332 --> 00:36:40,332
(Hyo Min finally smiles.)

863
00:36:40,333 --> 00:36:41,631
All right, Hyo Min?

864
00:36:41,632 --> 00:36:44,532
This stays between us.

865
00:36:45,342 --> 00:36:47,572
I'm really sorry. Let me give you a hug.

866
00:36:47,902 --> 00:36:49,112
I'm sorry.

867
00:36:50,072 --> 00:36:53,542
(I'm sorry, Hyo Min.)

868
00:36:54,142 --> 00:36:56,812
I'll make sure that you have fun with it.

869
00:36:58,482 --> 00:36:59,582
I'm serious.

870
00:36:59,852 --> 00:37:02,222
You'll have so much fun, playing the Scarecrow.

871
00:37:03,452 --> 00:37:06,922
Sorry. It's getting late, so let's get out of here.

872
00:37:07,062 --> 00:37:08,562
- Okay.
- Poor you.

873
00:37:09,232 --> 00:37:10,332
I'm sorry.

874
00:37:19,872 --> 00:37:21,672
- Bye.
- Bye.

875
00:37:22,242 --> 00:37:24,142
- Get home safely.
- Okay.

876
00:37:25,242 --> 00:37:26,842
- See you tomorrow, Hyo Min.
- Yes.

877
00:37:31,282 --> 00:37:32,851
- Bye.
- Bye.

878
00:37:32,852 --> 00:37:34,252
(After seeing Hyo Min off...)

879
00:38:06,722 --> 00:38:08,282
This is tough.

880
00:38:08,722 --> 00:38:09,852
Man.

881
00:38:14,792 --> 00:38:17,931
(She's worried...)

882
00:38:17,932 --> 00:38:22,872
(that her decision today could have scarred him.)

883
00:38:26,642 --> 00:38:28,202
To be perfectly honest,

884
00:38:28,912 --> 00:38:31,412
I actually took a few steps back.

885
00:38:35,752 --> 00:38:39,482
I tried to assign the roles based on their capacity.

886
00:38:39,552 --> 00:38:42,091
We're running out of time,

887
00:38:42,092 --> 00:38:44,221
so it's wise to give the roles...

888
00:38:44,222 --> 00:38:46,262
to the kids who can pull them off.

889
00:38:46,522 --> 00:38:49,292
I thought it was fair...

890
00:38:50,132 --> 00:38:52,402
not to assign difficult roles...

891
00:38:53,702 --> 00:38:56,402
to those who would have a hard time while playing them.

892
00:39:02,972 --> 00:39:04,142
After that,

893
00:39:05,512 --> 00:39:06,782
I went home,

894
00:39:07,642 --> 00:39:09,652
and the question notes...

895
00:39:12,252 --> 00:39:15,822
I opened Hyo Min's notes, wondering what he wrote.

896
00:39:17,522 --> 00:39:18,552
And it said...

897
00:39:22,732 --> 00:39:28,932
(She opened Hyo Min's question notes after class.)

898
00:39:38,642 --> 00:39:43,351
(On the page that she stared at for a long time...)

899
00:39:43,352 --> 00:39:48,451
(Ms. Kim, I want to play Toto. I practiced.)

900
00:39:48,452 --> 00:39:53,662
(Ms. Kim, I want to play Toto. I practiced.)

901
00:39:58,562 --> 00:40:04,602
(She realized what was truly on his mind a bit too late.)

902
00:40:08,742 --> 00:40:09,912
What do I do?

903
00:40:16,082 --> 00:40:17,212
What do I do?

904
00:40:24,252 --> 00:40:29,362
(She realizes what those tears meant.)

905
00:40:32,062 --> 00:40:33,901
He wrote that in his question notes,

906
00:40:33,902 --> 00:40:35,702
and even practiced at home.

907
00:40:36,232 --> 00:40:38,972
Then, he got a role that wasn't Toto.

908
00:40:39,472 --> 00:40:41,872
His reaction was natural.

909
00:40:42,412 --> 00:40:43,472
I wonder...

910
00:40:43,972 --> 00:40:46,681
why I didn't open that during class.

911
00:40:46,682 --> 00:40:48,952
(Why didn't I open it during class?)

912
00:40:54,382 --> 00:40:55,851
- Come here.
- What is it?

913
00:40:55,852 --> 00:40:59,762
(Hyun Wook walks in at that moment.)

914
00:41:15,072 --> 00:41:16,312
What should we do with Hyo Min?

915
00:41:16,812 --> 00:41:17,942
What do we do?

916
00:41:18,572 --> 00:41:20,241
But if we change Hyo Min's role now...

917
00:41:20,242 --> 00:41:21,242
Yes.

918
00:41:21,712 --> 00:41:24,812
That means Do Hyun loses Tin Man's role.

919
00:41:25,382 --> 00:41:26,551
Do you get what I mean?

920
00:41:26,552 --> 00:41:29,152
Do Hyun must be practicing right now.

921
00:41:32,052 --> 00:41:33,622
Did you just read that?

922
00:41:33,992 --> 00:41:36,592
Just now. I should have read it as soon as I got it.

923
00:41:38,832 --> 00:41:40,262
What do I do?

924
00:41:41,232 --> 00:41:43,172
Why didn't I read these before I assigned the roles?

925
00:41:43,772 --> 00:41:44,802
- Right?
- Yes.

926
00:41:45,072 --> 00:41:46,401
- Even yesterday, - Yes.

927
00:41:46,402 --> 00:41:49,211
- We had time.
- they practiced reading the script.

928
00:41:49,212 --> 00:41:50,412
Why didn't I read them?

929
00:41:52,242 --> 00:41:53,342
I don't know what to do.

930
00:41:55,042 --> 00:41:56,482
I felt terrible.

931
00:41:58,182 --> 00:42:00,222
He came to school with such high expectations...

932
00:42:00,982 --> 00:42:02,652
of getting the role that he wanted.

933
00:42:04,192 --> 00:42:06,791
He must have been so excited...

934
00:42:06,792 --> 00:42:08,762
when he practiced it.

935
00:42:09,432 --> 00:42:12,561
It must have doubled his disappointment.

936
00:42:12,562 --> 00:42:13,562
So,

937
00:42:14,902 --> 00:42:19,002
I totally understand Hyo Min's reaction today.

938
00:42:23,942 --> 00:42:24,942
Oh, man.

939
00:42:31,782 --> 00:42:35,821
The fact that Hyo Min practiced...

940
00:42:35,822 --> 00:42:38,251
(The fact that Hyo Min practiced...)

941
00:42:38,252 --> 00:42:40,662
Toto's role really hard...

942
00:42:43,232 --> 00:42:44,262
It just...

943
00:42:45,832 --> 00:42:47,131
broke my heart.

944
00:42:47,132 --> 00:42:49,732
(It broke my heart.)

945
00:42:53,642 --> 00:42:54,642
Jeez.

946
00:42:54,872 --> 00:42:58,612
(After his chat with Ms. Kim)

947
00:43:00,482 --> 00:43:02,212
Bye. Do you want a hug?

948
00:43:02,582 --> 00:43:03,851
Come here. No?

949
00:43:03,852 --> 00:43:04,912
Are you all right?

950
00:43:07,322 --> 00:43:09,552
Do you feel okay? You can do it, right?

951
00:43:10,292 --> 00:43:11,522
You've got this.

952
00:43:11,852 --> 00:43:14,562
You can also play the Scarecrow.

953
00:43:15,492 --> 00:43:17,932
You were being a bigger man...

954
00:43:18,262 --> 00:43:19,502
since Kyung Mo is too young.

955
00:43:20,162 --> 00:43:22,532
There's more that you can do.

956
00:43:24,872 --> 00:43:26,772
Let's play baseball together.

957
00:43:27,202 --> 00:43:28,741
When you're stressed,

958
00:43:28,742 --> 00:43:30,711
just ask me, "Let's play baseball,"

959
00:43:30,712 --> 00:43:32,512
and we'll go during recess.

960
00:43:33,012 --> 00:43:34,512
Okay? I promise.

961
00:43:35,182 --> 00:43:37,751
Run around while playing baseball, and you'll feel better.

962
00:43:37,752 --> 00:43:39,051
(He's not perfect, but he slowly becomes a teacher.)

963
00:43:39,052 --> 00:43:40,422
Get home safely.

964
00:43:40,952 --> 00:43:42,052
- See you tomorrow.
- See you.

965
00:43:45,286 --> 00:43:48,816
It's been so long since I starred in this kind of show.

966
00:43:49,786 --> 00:43:51,185
Hi, I'm Kangnam.

967
00:43:51,186 --> 00:43:53,196
It's nice to meet you.

968
00:43:54,996 --> 00:43:58,966
(Back after conquering the North Pole)

969
00:44:00,966 --> 00:44:02,036
It's so...

970
00:44:02,606 --> 00:44:05,505
(He's been on a school show before.)

971
00:44:05,506 --> 00:44:07,235
When I was on "Off to School,"

972
00:44:07,236 --> 00:44:08,935
those high school students cried.

973
00:44:08,936 --> 00:44:10,346
I still remember.

974
00:44:10,606 --> 00:44:11,875
So, I hope...

975
00:44:11,876 --> 00:44:14,146
those elementary school kids cry when we say goodbye.

976
00:44:14,546 --> 00:44:15,676
Guys, wait.

977
00:44:15,846 --> 00:44:19,686
(His dream comes true.)

978
00:44:20,586 --> 00:44:23,586
(There's no way. They're crying all day.)

979
00:44:23,786 --> 00:44:25,995
(Trying to escape)

980
00:44:25,996 --> 00:44:28,756
Those two must think they're the only ones on the show.

981
00:44:29,596 --> 00:44:31,826
They don't know who's coming or when you're coming.

982
00:44:33,166 --> 00:44:34,235
It sounds fun.

983
00:44:34,236 --> 00:44:37,006
You don't know who the new teacher is, right?

984
00:44:37,136 --> 00:44:40,076
That's the only thing I'm dying to know.

985
00:44:41,506 --> 00:44:42,806
When is the other one coming?

986
00:44:43,906 --> 00:44:45,605
I'm so curious.

987
00:44:45,606 --> 00:44:47,045
I think they'll be here tonight.

988
00:44:47,046 --> 00:44:48,375
(Their curiosity grows.)

989
00:44:48,376 --> 00:44:49,486
- The new teacher?
- Yes.

990
00:44:51,416 --> 00:44:53,315
Where's the new member?

991
00:44:53,316 --> 00:44:55,455
(They grow more desperate as days go by.)

992
00:44:55,456 --> 00:44:56,685
We're in the house...

993
00:44:56,686 --> 00:44:58,956
across Yongheung Elementary School in Mungyeong.

994
00:45:00,296 --> 00:45:02,296
This is an SOS video.

995
00:45:03,226 --> 00:45:05,026
It is urgent. Please come.

996
00:45:05,326 --> 00:45:07,636
I'll cook ramyeon for you. I'll treat you nicely.

997
00:45:08,096 --> 00:45:09,206
So, please come...

998
00:45:12,506 --> 00:45:13,836
and save everyone.

999
00:45:18,306 --> 00:45:21,775
(The man answered their prayers.)

1000
00:45:21,776 --> 00:45:24,546
It's beautiful. This place looks nice.

1001
00:45:25,786 --> 00:45:26,985
It looks like a filming set.

1002
00:45:26,986 --> 00:45:30,255
(He arrives while they're in class.)

1003
00:45:30,256 --> 00:45:31,386
What's this?

1004
00:45:36,866 --> 00:45:38,926
It's a beautiful house.

1005
00:45:44,036 --> 00:45:46,276
I guess they're not that organized.

1006
00:45:48,876 --> 00:45:50,776
Oh, like this. It's warm.

1007
00:45:51,676 --> 00:45:52,716
How spacious.

1008
00:45:55,946 --> 00:45:57,886
Where's the bathroom? Here?

1009
00:46:01,986 --> 00:46:03,255
It's not. There's no bathroom.

1010
00:46:03,256 --> 00:46:05,656
(There's no bathroom?)

1011
00:46:06,856 --> 00:46:08,426
It's very cozy.

1012
00:46:10,696 --> 00:46:12,426
So, they're teaching over there.

1013
00:46:13,966 --> 00:46:15,695
- Well done, me.
- Okay?

1014
00:46:15,696 --> 00:46:17,735
Compliment yourself.

1015
00:46:17,736 --> 00:46:18,765
Okay.

1016
00:46:18,766 --> 00:46:19,836
Oh, no.

1017
00:46:20,806 --> 00:46:23,306
I feel conflicted.

1018
00:46:27,076 --> 00:46:32,086
(He chose a bad day to join them.)

1019
00:46:37,586 --> 00:46:39,956
I bet they never had delicious food here,

1020
00:46:41,326 --> 00:46:43,665
judging from how messy the house is. I should cook for them.

1021
00:46:43,666 --> 00:46:44,966
(Making dinner for the hardworking teachers)

1022
00:46:45,226 --> 00:46:46,535
I'm sure they're craving some homemade food by now.

1023
00:46:46,536 --> 00:46:48,796
(He chops the vegetables and meat that he bought.)

1024
00:46:50,006 --> 00:46:52,466
(Using various condiments)

1025
00:46:54,136 --> 00:46:55,705
(Boil them with water,)

1026
00:46:55,706 --> 00:46:57,205
(and the gochujang stew is ready.)

1027
00:46:57,206 --> 00:46:58,276
Good.

1028
00:46:58,876 --> 00:46:59,876
Oil.

1029
00:46:59,877 --> 00:47:01,316
(Next, he makes fried rice.)

1030
00:47:02,686 --> 00:47:04,585
(Putting green onion oil,)

1031
00:47:04,586 --> 00:47:06,915
(instant rice, and scrambled eggs into one frying pan)

1032
00:47:06,916 --> 00:47:07,916
And then...

1033
00:47:10,656 --> 00:47:14,426
(He shapes the fried rice nicely.)

1034
00:47:15,126 --> 00:47:17,196
(The last dish is...)

1035
00:47:17,996 --> 00:47:21,766
(grilled mackerel.)

1036
00:47:23,006 --> 00:47:26,476
(He sets up a table of food in an instant.)

1037
00:47:30,476 --> 00:47:32,845
Sang Hwa would scold me so much if I made this mess at home.

1038
00:47:32,846 --> 00:47:34,216
This place is easy.

1039
00:47:35,516 --> 00:47:37,186
I like how no one can nag at me.

1040
00:47:39,716 --> 00:47:40,886
Let's leave it at that.

1041
00:47:42,316 --> 00:47:43,685
I'll hide here.

1042
00:47:43,686 --> 00:47:47,326
(I'll hide here.)

1043
00:47:49,726 --> 00:47:51,465
What did you do with the apple that you were eating?

1044
00:47:51,466 --> 00:47:52,495
- Did you leave it there?
- I left it.

1045
00:47:52,496 --> 00:47:54,496
(Tae Ri and Potato return home after class.)

1046
00:47:58,766 --> 00:48:00,206
Oh, we left the window open.

1047
00:48:01,806 --> 00:48:02,846
What?

1048
00:48:09,586 --> 00:48:10,646
It's food!

1049
00:48:11,786 --> 00:48:13,356
Don't do this to us.

1050
00:48:14,416 --> 00:48:15,485
What is this?

1051
00:48:15,486 --> 00:48:17,486
(An unknown table of food greets them.)

1052
00:48:18,226 --> 00:48:19,285
Who did this?

1053
00:48:19,286 --> 00:48:20,426
This is so...

1054
00:48:22,556 --> 00:48:23,596
What?

1055
00:48:24,396 --> 00:48:25,426
Where are they?

1056
00:48:26,966 --> 00:48:28,396
- What...
- What's going on?

1057
00:48:30,706 --> 00:48:31,866
This is fun, Tae Ri.

1058
00:48:34,576 --> 00:48:35,636
Where...

1059
00:48:38,346 --> 00:48:40,546
Did they make it here? They did, right?

1060
00:48:40,946 --> 00:48:43,315
They cooked it here. This is really happening.

1061
00:48:43,316 --> 00:48:44,515
It's for real.

1062
