1318
01:00:41,832 --> 01:00:43,072
- I don't know.
- I know.

1319
01:00:43,602 --> 01:00:45,442
I think it was too hot when we were sleeping.

1320
01:00:46,772 --> 01:00:49,442
We were grilled. It was like a sauna.

1321
01:00:51,982 --> 01:00:54,182
I think Tae Ri turned up the heater.

1322
01:00:55,012 --> 01:00:56,082
It wasn't so hot before.

1323
01:00:56,612 --> 01:00:58,621
I think she only meant to make her room warmer,

1324
01:00:58,622 --> 01:00:59,981
but our room got warmer too.

1325
01:00:59,982 --> 01:01:02,752
(It seems like Tae Ri's passion warmed up the floors.)

1326
01:01:03,322 --> 01:01:04,592
Do you run every day?

1327
01:01:04,762 --> 01:01:06,391
- Almost every day. Yes.
- Almost?

1328
01:01:06,392 --> 01:01:07,791
- I do in Seoul.
- In Seoul.

1329
01:01:07,792 --> 01:01:09,032
- Yes.
- Where do you go? Han River?

1330
01:01:09,162 --> 01:01:10,562
Yes. Han River.

1331
01:01:10,832 --> 01:01:12,961
- Also, Mount Maebong.
- I see, Mount Maebong.

1332
01:01:12,962 --> 01:01:14,832
I sometimes run there.

1333
01:01:18,742 --> 01:01:21,341
Right, tell me about your dream.

1334
01:01:21,342 --> 01:01:22,342
My dream?

1335
01:01:22,542 --> 01:01:23,912
- I was suddenly shooting...
- Yes?

1336
01:01:24,182 --> 01:01:26,311
- a drama series.
- Okay.

1337
01:01:26,312 --> 01:01:28,811
- Since it was so sudden, - Yes?

1338
01:01:28,812 --> 01:01:30,112
- I didn't know the lines.
- Right.

1339
01:01:30,722 --> 01:01:32,252
So Tae Ri taught me...

1340
01:01:32,452 --> 01:01:34,652
the lines from the beginning to the end.

1341
01:01:35,392 --> 01:01:37,022
- But I couldn't understand.
- Okay.

1342
01:01:37,262 --> 01:01:39,392
- I was so stressed.
- I see.

1343
01:01:39,622 --> 01:01:41,461
- Really?
- I was so stressed.

1344
01:01:41,462 --> 01:01:42,762
I'm looking forward to today.

1345
01:01:44,532 --> 01:01:45,802
I was so stressed.

1346
01:01:47,732 --> 01:01:50,502
Dear villagers, the general store truck is here.

1347
01:01:51,102 --> 01:01:53,272
- Please come to the town hall.
- What is that?

1348
01:01:53,612 --> 01:01:55,212
Are all the grannies here?

1349
01:01:56,412 --> 01:01:58,681
What? What is that? What are they doing?

1350
01:01:58,682 --> 01:01:59,682
(It's a popular place.)

1351
01:01:59,683 --> 01:02:01,552
Right, like "Our Blues."

1352
01:02:02,752 --> 01:02:04,082
Like "Our Blues."

1353
01:02:04,222 --> 01:02:06,052
I have a gold axe and a silver axe.

1354
01:02:06,922 --> 01:02:08,221
- They come around selling things.
- Yes.

1355
01:02:08,222 --> 01:02:09,251
(Someone who looked like Eugene Choi was driving it around.)

1356
01:02:09,252 --> 01:02:10,462
What do you call that?

1357
01:02:10,792 --> 01:02:12,692
(General store truck: Feel free to order...)

1358
01:02:12,922 --> 01:02:14,231
(Beef, pork, chicken, octopus, squid...)

1359
01:02:14,232 --> 01:02:15,932
(Chicken gizzard, chicken feet, smoked duck...)

1360
01:02:16,632 --> 01:02:17,701
It's my first time seeing it.

1361
01:02:17,702 --> 01:02:20,471
(They have what they have, and don't have what they don't.)

1362
01:02:20,472 --> 01:02:21,532
This is interesting.

1363
01:02:22,232 --> 01:02:25,472
(The general store truck magically appears and disappears.)

1364
01:02:27,112 --> 01:02:28,942
- Hello.
- Hello.

1365
01:02:29,042 --> 01:02:30,511
- Amazing.
- What?

1366
01:02:30,512 --> 01:02:32,411
Hey, they have everything.

1367
01:02:32,412 --> 01:02:33,412
(These city boys are impressed by the truck.)

1368
01:02:33,413 --> 01:02:35,351
- Here it is.
- The ladies are going crazy.

1369
01:02:35,352 --> 01:02:37,951
- No, something bigger.
- Bigger?

1370
01:02:37,952 --> 01:02:40,081
I didn't know it was real.

1371
01:02:40,082 --> 01:02:41,092
(They're going to go crazy soon too.)

1372
01:02:41,252 --> 01:02:43,192
- Should we buy something? Jjajang?
- Should we?

1373
01:02:43,252 --> 01:02:44,991
- Jjajang is a good idea.
- This one?

1374
01:02:44,992 --> 01:02:46,022
The jjajang sauce.

1375
01:02:46,062 --> 01:02:47,492
They have kalguksu too.

1376
01:02:47,962 --> 01:02:50,032
- Let's have some.
- I'd like that.

1377
01:02:50,532 --> 01:02:51,761
Kalguksu will be good.

1378
01:02:51,762 --> 01:02:53,201
(Impulsive shopping list: Kalguksu noodles)

1379
01:02:53,202 --> 01:02:54,701
- Right?
- Should we get this too?

1380
01:02:54,702 --> 01:02:55,771
Let's buy it too.

1381
01:02:55,772 --> 01:02:57,601
- Do they only have two?
- I don't know.

1382
01:02:57,602 --> 01:02:58,602
(Jjajang sauce)

1383
01:02:58,742 --> 01:03:00,542
Sir. Wait, who is the owner?

1384
01:03:02,012 --> 01:03:03,042
Who owns this truck?

1385
01:03:03,072 --> 01:03:04,241
Are you the owner?

1386
01:03:04,242 --> 01:03:05,281
- No.
- No?

1387
01:03:05,282 --> 01:03:06,942
He looks like the owner for sure.

1388
01:03:08,082 --> 01:03:10,921
He looks like the owner. Are you not?

1389
01:03:10,922 --> 01:03:12,252
- Really?
- He's a villager.

1390
01:03:12,352 --> 01:03:14,491
Where is the owner?

1391
01:03:14,492 --> 01:03:16,421
- Hello.
- Hello.

1392
01:03:16,422 --> 01:03:17,861
- Do you have more jjajang sauce?
- Yes.

1393
01:03:17,862 --> 01:03:20,462
Jjajang sauce? Yes, I have more.

1394
01:03:21,232 --> 01:03:22,492
- Jjajang.
- Yes.

1395
01:03:23,062 --> 01:03:24,901
What kind of ingredients do we need for kalguksu?

1396
01:03:24,902 --> 01:03:26,262
Zucchini? We have zucchini.

1397
01:03:27,632 --> 01:03:28,632
What should we buy?

1398
01:03:28,972 --> 01:03:30,702
- We have pepper already.
- We have pepper.

1399
01:03:31,342 --> 01:03:33,401
You need zucchini and cabbage for kalguksu.

1400
01:03:33,402 --> 01:03:34,471
- Cabbage?
- Yes.

1401
01:03:34,472 --> 01:03:36,511
- Do we need anything?
- No. We have everything.

1402
01:03:36,512 --> 01:03:38,212
Right, do they have meat?

1403
01:03:38,382 --> 01:03:40,511
I don't think they have meat. Am I right?

1404
01:03:40,512 --> 01:03:41,811
- There's no meat.
- Right?

1405
01:03:41,812 --> 01:03:43,012
They don't have any.

1406
01:03:43,152 --> 01:03:44,381
- You look like an actor.
- Am I handsome?

1407
01:03:44,382 --> 01:03:46,421
- Yes, you're handsome.
- Do I look like an actor?

1408
01:03:46,422 --> 01:03:48,121
- Yes. I fell in love.
- Really?

1409
01:03:48,122 --> 01:03:49,622
(The compliment makes Hyun Wook smile.)

1410
01:03:49,922 --> 01:03:51,391
Do you have meat?

1411
01:03:51,392 --> 01:03:53,322
- Yes, I do.
- Please give me some.

1412
01:03:53,892 --> 01:03:56,491
- Do you want pork belly?
- Pork belly.

1413
01:03:56,492 --> 01:03:58,032
- Pork belly.
- They have meat?

1414
01:03:58,262 --> 01:03:59,701
- Let's have it tonight.
- Okay.

1415
01:03:59,702 --> 01:04:00,871
We have one at home.

1416
01:04:00,872 --> 01:04:02,802
- Should we eat them together? Good.
- Yes.

1417
01:04:03,002 --> 01:04:04,071
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

1418
01:04:04,072 --> 01:04:05,072
(Their hands are full from the purchase.)

1419
01:04:05,073 --> 01:04:06,401
- Bye.
- Bye.

1420
01:04:06,402 --> 01:04:08,271
- You should come watch the play.
- Okay.

1421
01:04:08,272 --> 01:04:11,581
Come watch the play on November 11th.

1422
01:04:11,582 --> 01:04:12,941
- Where at?
- At the school.

1423
01:04:12,942 --> 01:04:14,182
Yongheung Elementary School.

1424
01:04:14,412 --> 01:04:16,351
- When?
- On the 11th.

1425
01:04:16,352 --> 01:04:17,352
(They didn't forget to promote the play.)

1426
01:04:17,353 --> 01:04:18,822
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

1427
01:04:20,992 --> 01:04:22,151
Are we having meat for dinner?

1428
01:04:22,152 --> 01:04:23,392
- Yes, for dinner.
- Okay.

1429
01:04:23,492 --> 01:04:25,522
- Although I want to eat it now.
- Sure.

1430
01:04:27,362 --> 01:04:30,192
(Meanwhile, Ms. Kim...)

1431
01:04:31,502 --> 01:04:34,572
(is leaving responses on the question notes.)

1432
01:04:36,932 --> 01:04:37,941
(Screaming)

1433
01:04:37,942 --> 01:04:39,042
Hi.

1434
01:04:41,112 --> 01:04:43,142
(She is easily scared.)

1435
01:04:43,442 --> 01:04:44,512
Let's eat breakfast.

1436
01:04:44,782 --> 01:04:45,941
- Did you buy something?
- Yes.

1437
01:04:45,942 --> 01:04:47,082
What is it?

1438
01:04:47,152 --> 01:04:48,212
Today's menu?

1439
01:04:48,682 --> 01:04:49,951
- Kalguksu.
- Kalguksu.

1440
01:04:49,952 --> 01:04:51,952
- Is that breakfast?
- Breakfast is kalguksu.

1441
01:04:52,522 --> 01:04:54,092
- Really?
- Yes.

1442
01:04:56,452 --> 01:04:57,662
Should I make braised tofu?

1443
01:04:57,922 --> 01:04:59,092
- That sounds nice.
- Right?

1444
01:04:59,692 --> 01:05:01,432
It won't be enough to eat just kalguksu alone.

1445
01:05:06,132 --> 01:05:09,032
(Kangnam is in charge of kalguksu.)

1446
01:05:10,002 --> 01:05:12,372
(Preparing the vegetables first)

1447
01:05:14,972 --> 01:05:16,842
(Boiling the noodles)

1448
01:05:17,182 --> 01:05:18,581
Sprinkle some chili powder.

1449
01:05:18,582 --> 01:05:19,712
(Sprinkling chili powder for spice)

1450
01:05:22,752 --> 01:05:24,952
(Slurping)

1451
01:05:26,782 --> 01:05:28,492
(Satisfied)

1452
01:05:30,492 --> 01:05:31,791
You made it so fast.

1453
01:05:31,792 --> 01:05:33,992
(The main menu is finished in a flash.)

1454
01:05:34,562 --> 01:05:36,161
- I made too much.
- Okay.

1455
01:05:36,162 --> 01:05:37,332
Way too much.

1456
01:05:38,062 --> 01:05:40,572
Our breakfast became so fancy after Kangnam joined.

1457
01:05:41,902 --> 01:05:43,032
Braised tofu sounds delicious.

1458
01:05:43,102 --> 01:05:44,401
- Right?
- It sounds so good.

1459
01:05:44,402 --> 01:05:45,472
(Hyun Wook is in charge of the braised tofu.)

1460
01:05:46,672 --> 01:05:48,812
(Making the sauce first)

1461
01:05:49,372 --> 01:05:51,812
(Staring)

1462
01:05:52,282 --> 01:05:54,282
(When you're unsure of a recipe, check videos online.)

1463
01:05:57,852 --> 01:06:00,451
(It's going smoothly thanks to the online recipe.)

1464
01:06:00,452 --> 01:06:02,052
Are you making different dishes?

1465
01:06:02,152 --> 01:06:03,222
Yes.

1466
01:06:04,222 --> 01:06:06,021
- What are you making?
- Braised tofu.

1467
01:06:06,022 --> 01:06:07,192
(My name is braised tofu.)

1468
01:06:08,462 --> 01:06:10,602
(Making green onion oil)

1469
01:06:11,762 --> 01:06:13,662
(Pouring the sauce on top)

1470
01:06:14,232 --> 01:06:15,671
- It smells so good.
- Gosh.

1471
01:06:15,672 --> 01:06:16,801
It smells good.

1472
01:06:16,802 --> 01:06:17,941
It was white just a second ago.

1473
01:06:17,942 --> 01:06:19,471
That should be eaten with rice.

1474
01:06:19,472 --> 01:06:20,472
(It makes them crave rice.)

1475
01:06:20,742 --> 01:06:23,172
- Should I make some rice?
- Yes.

1476
01:06:23,242 --> 01:06:24,511
- Right?
- Are you making rice?

1477
01:06:24,512 --> 01:06:26,142
- Yes.
- But we have so many noodles.

1478
01:06:26,442 --> 01:06:27,651
- We'll have them together.
- Together.

1479
01:06:27,652 --> 01:06:30,182
We're really hungry because we ran.

1480
01:06:31,882 --> 01:06:33,182
- Is this good enough?
- Yes.

1481
01:06:33,822 --> 01:06:34,992
It's good enough.

1482
01:06:35,192 --> 01:06:36,751
We need rice for that.

1483
01:06:36,752 --> 01:06:37,762
It looks so good.

1484
01:06:39,292 --> 01:06:41,291
Gosh, it looks amazing.

1485
01:06:41,292 --> 01:06:42,292
(Their first breakfast together)

1486
01:06:42,792 --> 01:06:44,302
The soup is disappearing. Let's hurry up and eat.

1487
01:06:44,632 --> 01:06:46,862
- Thank you for the food.
- Thank you for the food.

1488
01:06:48,772 --> 01:06:51,702
(Having a mouthful of the noodles first)

1489
01:06:52,942 --> 01:06:55,472
(Slurping everywhere)

1490
01:06:56,172 --> 01:06:57,381
- Is it okay?
- Yes.

1491
01:06:57,382 --> 01:06:58,412
It's good.

1492
01:06:59,012 --> 01:07:00,142
Hey!

1493
01:07:01,282 --> 01:07:02,412
Gosh.

1494
01:07:02,612 --> 01:07:03,751
The tofu is good.

1495
01:07:03,752 --> 01:07:04,752
(Expressing with his eyebrows)

1496
01:07:05,622 --> 01:07:07,952
(Tae Ri is taking a bite of the braised tofu too.)

1497
01:07:08,422 --> 01:07:09,492
Isn't it good?

1498
01:07:09,992 --> 01:07:12,421
- We bought this at the market.
- This would be so good with rice.

1499
01:07:12,422 --> 01:07:13,492
Right? Isn't it delicious?

1500
01:07:17,192 --> 01:07:19,302
(Slurping)

1501
01:07:20,932 --> 01:07:23,332
(Expressing with his face)

1502
01:07:24,572 --> 01:07:26,872
(This runner is busy filling up his empty stomach.)

1503
01:07:28,412 --> 01:07:29,572
Thank you for breakfast.

1504
01:07:32,642 --> 01:07:36,752
Now that we're a team, let's cheer together.

1505
01:07:37,322 --> 01:07:38,682
- Let's do one.
- Okay, sure.

1506
01:07:39,482 --> 01:07:41,122
How about, "Let's go, Curtain Up, Class!"

1507
01:07:41,352 --> 01:07:43,962
- I like it. Let's go!
- How is North Pole Teacher?

1508
01:07:44,392 --> 01:07:45,462
"North Pole Teacher?"

1509
01:07:45,662 --> 01:07:47,331
"North Pole Teacher?" Not bad.

1510
01:07:47,332 --> 01:07:49,632
Or how about...

1511
01:07:49,832 --> 01:07:51,901
- Just hurry up and decide.
- Polar Bear Teacher.

1512
01:07:51,902 --> 01:07:52,962
- What?
- Polar Bear Teacher.

1513
01:07:53,102 --> 01:07:54,271
"Polar Bear Teacher?"

1514
01:07:54,272 --> 01:07:55,301
(Building friendship over sweaty hands)

1515
01:07:55,302 --> 01:07:56,831
- North Pole Teacher.
- North Pole Teacher.

1516
01:07:56,832 --> 01:07:58,071
(They miraculously agree.)

1517
01:07:58,072 --> 01:07:59,341
Okay.

1518
01:07:59,342 --> 01:08:01,511
- Curtain Up, Class! Ms. Kim.
- Potato Teacher.

1519
01:08:01,512 --> 01:08:03,511
- North Pole Teacher.
- Let's go!

1520
01:08:03,512 --> 01:08:04,782
Yes.

1521
01:08:05,042 --> 01:08:06,311
We have to get ready and leave right now.

1522
01:08:06,312 --> 01:08:07,582
Yes.

1523
01:08:07,782 --> 01:08:11,021
I wonder what kind of day will unfold today.

1524
01:08:11,022 --> 01:08:12,482
I finally get to see the kids.

1525
01:08:14,052 --> 01:08:15,921
How do you feel? Nervous? Or excited?

1526
01:08:15,922 --> 01:08:17,191
I'm excited to meet them.

1527
01:08:17,192 --> 01:08:19,292
(Looking forward to North Pole Teacher's hot debut)

1528
01:08:20,792 --> 01:08:22,891
This is our fifth class today.

1529
01:08:22,892 --> 01:08:24,102
(5th class)

1530
01:08:24,702 --> 01:08:26,762
(Today's class will be held in the yard...)

1531
01:08:27,872 --> 01:08:28,872
This is how.

1532
01:08:28,873 --> 01:08:29,902
(with North Pole Teacher.)

1533
01:08:31,142 --> 01:08:34,612
(It's the first joint class with the three teachers.)

1534
01:08:35,542 --> 01:08:37,211
- Hyun Wook, when warming up, - Yes.

1535
01:08:37,212 --> 01:08:39,882
are you going to do the signature thing?

1536
01:08:39,982 --> 01:08:41,112
What's the signature thing?

1537
01:08:41,282 --> 01:08:42,611
They'll think of a signature move...

1538
01:08:42,612 --> 01:08:45,082
- for each character.
- Right.

1539
01:08:45,652 --> 01:08:47,122
- And they'll try it.
- Okay.

1540
01:08:47,592 --> 01:08:49,521
- Are we doing it today?
- Should I not?

1541
01:08:49,522 --> 01:08:51,422
Each character... Yes, I want you to do it.

1542
01:08:51,592 --> 01:08:52,961
Okay. From now...

1543
01:08:52,962 --> 01:08:56,361
Each one of you has a role to play.

1544
01:08:56,362 --> 01:08:57,662
So...

1545
01:08:57,732 --> 01:09:01,102
Think about your character and come up with...

1546
01:09:01,432 --> 01:09:03,602
a signature move of the character. Do I say that?

1547
01:09:05,572 --> 01:09:07,072
What did you think this was?

1548
01:09:08,142 --> 01:09:09,472
This is what's happening.

1549
01:09:10,742 --> 01:09:13,241
When I try to explain, I can't speak well.

1550
01:09:13,242 --> 01:09:14,582
- You can't speak?
- I mean...

1551
01:09:15,852 --> 01:09:17,111
- I mean...
- You can't speak?

1552
01:09:17,112 --> 01:09:18,622
- You mean it's hard to explain.
- I mean...

1553
01:09:19,182 --> 01:09:21,721
- In my head, I can explain it.
- Right.

1554
01:09:21,722 --> 01:09:22,751
Tae Ri, you know what I'm saying, right?

1555
01:09:22,752 --> 01:09:24,392
- Then you have to practice it.
- Got it.

1556
01:09:24,792 --> 01:09:25,922
Once I do it, I'm good at it.

1557
01:09:25,962 --> 01:09:28,262
Now, you know what role you're playing, right?

1558
01:09:28,432 --> 01:09:30,191
You'll express your role with your body.

1559
01:09:30,192 --> 01:09:31,702
How are you going to describe Scarecrow?

1560
01:09:32,162 --> 01:09:34,632
I'll walk around, and when I run into you,

1561
01:09:35,772 --> 01:09:36,931
why don't you say hello?

1562
01:09:36,932 --> 01:09:39,472
(His eyes met Tae Ri's.)

1563
01:09:40,942 --> 01:09:41,971
Please help him.

1564
01:09:41,972 --> 01:09:43,811
- Pretend to be the student.
- Why are you scared of her?

1565
01:09:43,812 --> 01:09:45,341
- Pretend to be a kid.
- He's scared of you.

1566
01:09:45,342 --> 01:09:46,382
Darn.

1567
01:09:46,712 --> 01:09:47,881
He keeps on checking...

1568
01:09:47,882 --> 01:09:50,052
- your reaction.
- Hey, if you act like that,

1569
01:09:50,112 --> 01:09:53,422
- He's checking if he's doing okay.
- what would the new teacher think?

1570
01:09:53,752 --> 01:09:56,151
How many years have we...

1571
01:09:56,152 --> 01:09:57,222
I know.

1572
01:09:57,522 --> 01:09:59,622
- You got this, right?
- Yes. I can really do it.

1573
01:09:59,762 --> 01:10:02,391
- We've spent an eternity together.
- Yes. Seriously.

1574
01:10:02,392 --> 01:10:03,961
- A lot has happened.
- Exactly.

1575
01:10:03,962 --> 01:10:05,131
- You have to come through, right?
- Yes.

1576
01:10:05,132 --> 01:10:06,931
You have to show that to the North Pole Teacher.

1577
01:10:06,932 --> 01:10:08,102
- Got it?
- Yes.

1578
01:10:08,202 --> 01:10:10,072
Let's go.

1579
01:10:10,372 --> 01:10:12,142
Be flexible. Open your heart.

1580
01:10:13,072 --> 01:10:14,811
- I'll assume the kids are here.
- Okay.

1581
01:10:14,812 --> 01:10:17,712
This is what we're going to do for the warmup.

1582
01:10:18,312 --> 01:10:20,282
Please pretend to be one of the kids.

1583
01:10:20,642 --> 01:10:22,551
- Mr. Choi, show us a lion.
- Lion?

1584
01:10:22,552 --> 01:10:23,611
A strong lion.

1585
01:10:23,612 --> 01:10:26,852
Show us an extremely strong lion that lives in Africa.

1586
01:10:27,892 --> 01:10:29,021
(Growling)

1587
01:10:29,022 --> 01:10:30,451
That one is from the zoo.

1588
01:10:30,452 --> 01:10:33,022
Please show us the strong one living in Africa.

1589
01:10:33,792 --> 01:10:36,392
(I'll show you my lion.)

1590
01:10:37,632 --> 01:10:38,862
It's the same as before.

1591
01:10:40,902 --> 01:10:42,072
It's the same as before.

1592
01:10:42,972 --> 01:10:45,242
- You come here.
- "You come here."

1593
01:10:45,442 --> 01:10:46,471
You come here.

1594
01:10:46,472 --> 01:10:48,511
(The main character is cast again.)

1595
01:10:48,512 --> 01:10:49,912
- "You come here." - Here.

1596
01:10:50,142 --> 01:10:52,081
It's been a while since I heard that.

1597
01:10:52,082 --> 01:10:53,181
("Weak Teacher," the skit)

1598
01:10:53,182 --> 01:10:54,611
"You come here."

1599
01:10:54,612 --> 01:10:56,552
- It's been so long.
- Do I have to crawl on all fours?

1600
01:10:56,782 --> 01:10:58,022
- No.
- What do I do?

1601
01:10:58,082 --> 01:11:00,051
- Hyun Wook, what's acting?
- Yes. Acting?

1602
01:11:00,052 --> 01:11:02,121
Hundreds of people watch you when you act.

1603
01:11:02,122 --> 01:11:04,191
- They weren't like these cameras.
- They are all watching you.

1604
01:11:04,192 --> 01:11:05,321
How do you act at that moment?

1605
01:11:05,322 --> 01:11:07,191
- You do it shamelessly, right?
- Yes.

1606
01:11:07,192 --> 01:11:08,432
Are you really a thug?

1607
01:11:08,762 --> 01:11:10,831
- You're not an actual thug.
- No.

1608
01:11:10,832 --> 01:11:12,531
- But you act one.
- I do.

1609
01:11:12,532 --> 01:11:13,931
- Okay?
- She's right.

1610
01:11:13,932 --> 01:11:15,171
You have to exaggerate it threefold.

1611
01:11:15,172 --> 01:11:16,532
She's on point.

1612
01:11:17,372 --> 01:11:19,942
(Now, North Pole Teacher makes an entrance.)

1613
01:11:20,442 --> 01:11:21,442
Are you going...

1614
01:11:21,443 --> 01:11:22,842
- to make a grand entrance?
- Yes, a grand one.

1615
01:11:23,072 --> 01:11:24,142
How?

1616
01:11:24,612 --> 01:11:25,712
How grand will it be?

1617
01:11:27,812 --> 01:11:29,752
(Growling weakly)

1618
01:11:31,482 --> 01:11:33,321
You two are the same.

1619
01:11:33,322 --> 01:11:35,292
- Relax.
- Okay. I'll relax.

1620
01:11:36,192 --> 01:11:38,192
- Are they coming now?
- Not yet.

1621
01:11:39,592 --> 01:11:41,831
This gazebo is lovely.

1622
01:11:41,832 --> 01:11:43,032
(After preparing the class...)

1623
01:11:44,632 --> 01:11:46,062
Let's take a photo.

1624
01:11:50,272 --> 01:11:52,042
One, two, three.

1625
01:11:54,712 --> 01:11:56,412
How unique. It looks like an old photo, right?

1626
01:11:56,512 --> 01:11:57,542
Yes.

1627
01:11:57,942 --> 01:11:59,682
- There's no bathroom.
- Really?

1628
01:12:00,112 --> 01:12:01,252
What? I have to go.

1629
01:12:01,312 --> 01:12:02,312
I'll hide.

1630
01:12:02,313 --> 01:12:04,011
- It's starting.
- Let's do this, everyone.

1631
01:12:04,012 --> 01:12:05,581
- Let's do that one.
- What?

1632
01:12:05,582 --> 01:12:07,152
Curtain Up, Class! Ms. Kim!

1633
01:12:07,652 --> 01:12:09,392
- Potato Teacher!
- North Pole Teacher!

1634
01:12:09,922 --> 01:12:11,122
- Let's go!
- Let's go!

1635
01:12:12,162 --> 01:12:14,231
What will happen?

1636
01:12:14,232 --> 01:12:15,932
(What will happen in today's class?)

1637
01:12:16,792 --> 01:12:19,962
(North Pole Teacher's first class)

1638
01:12:20,062 --> 01:12:21,372
What do you think?

1639
01:12:23,232 --> 01:12:24,942
(They are especially quiet today.)

1640
01:12:25,542 --> 01:12:27,002
(We're in trouble.)

1641
01:12:27,972 --> 01:12:30,412
(After the newbie's rough first day,)

1642
01:12:31,112 --> 01:12:33,642
(they held a barbecue party to welcome the new family.)

1643
01:12:34,612 --> 01:12:36,112
(The main chef brings out a smoky flavor.)

1644
01:12:36,912 --> 01:12:39,222
(Tae Ri is in charge of the rejuvenation.)

1645
01:12:40,322 --> 01:12:44,052
(The oldest one takes care of the younger ones.)

1646
01:12:44,992 --> 01:12:48,162
(The young brother takes care of the older sister.)

1647
01:12:49,532 --> 01:12:52,662
(They don't forget to rejuvenate during the weekend.)

1648
01:12:53,362 --> 01:12:54,732
(It's so pretty.)

1649
01:12:55,302 --> 01:12:56,932
(And...)

1650
01:12:57,532 --> 01:12:59,372
(CODE KUNST joins them as a music director.)

1651
01:13:00,242 --> 01:13:03,042
(Premiere of Music Director CO KUN's number)

1652
01:13:04,282 --> 01:13:07,482
(Ms. Kim is completely satisfied.)

1653
01:13:08,282 --> 01:13:10,652
(Asking for more while she's at it)

1654
01:13:13,082 --> 01:13:15,152
(I'll imagine it tonight while lying in bed.)

1655
01:13:16,022 --> 01:13:18,422
(The co-living of 4 members in the Mushroom House begins.)

1656
01:13:18,922 --> 01:13:20,162
(I feel totally reassured.)

1657
01:13:21,632 --> 01:13:22,932
(But where will CO KUN sleep?)

1658
01:13:23,662 --> 01:13:26,332
(And with that statement, the battle for the caravan begins.)

1659
01:13:26,502 --> 01:13:28,102
I think it's me.

1660
01:13:28,832 --> 01:13:31,142
(The irreversible ladder game to determine their fate)

1661
01:13:31,372 --> 01:13:33,342
- The caravan.
- Ta-da!

1662
01:13:34,272 --> 01:13:37,012
(Who will get the caravan?)

1663
01:13:37,754 --> 01:13:39,754
Dramaday.me
